error.signature: An error occurred (NoSuchBucket) when calling the ListObjects operation: The specified bucket does not exist

verdict.summary: The S3 bucket doesn't exist or the name is wrong.

dead_ends.action: Creating a new bucket with the same name
dead_ends.why_fails: S3 bucket names are globally unique; may be taken
Bucket doesn't exist; no policy to change

workarounds.action: Verify the bucket name: aws s3 ls — check for typos (names are case-sensitive, lowercase only)
workarounds.how: S3 bucket names must be globally unique and DNS-compliant

workarounds.action: Check the region — S3 bucket names are global but access may require the correct region endpoint
workarounds.how: Use --region flag: aws s3 ls s3://bucket --region us-west-2
